{
  "stem": "26672.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it just came, came to, back to me, asking what I remembered about my father.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was one instant where he was walking through the streets.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was grabbed by Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was taken to the barber shop to cut his beard off.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And for those people that-- if you know any orthodox people, Hasidic people, it's one of the worst things they can experience to have their beards cut off.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember, when he they was taking him to the barber shop, and the barber started cutting off his beard.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he finished halfway, one side, and the German left the room.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So my father put a scarf on, as though he had an earache, and he went out in the street.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's what I remember about my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The other thing I forgot to mention, at the beginning, where it was still a time before the war, and you asked me, what sect my-- Hasidic sect of my father?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember, my father taking me one day-- one year to see the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we went by train to [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[POLISH] is just outside Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he bought golden cherries, the white cherries.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And every time I see them now, I have to buy them, whatever the price is.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other thing is, when we moved into our home, the last home we lived in, before the war, was a brick-built.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the rabbi came for what we call [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], the housewarming, to bless our house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, the whole family moved out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was just the rabbi and his close-- And I remember sitting on his lap.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he gave me a coin, we call [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], blessed-- a blessed coin.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
